This paper is about the design of a machine learning architecture for spoken language understanding (SLU) in virtual digital assistants. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper emphasizes the flexibility and rapid iteration cycle for third-party developers, which could place it in the software engineering category (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the removal of significant barriers to entry for software developers and dialog systems researchers, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC) categories.
